  "text": "This model is particularly appropriate for our experiment. For one thing, the performance of collective operations often dominates overall performance in distributed applications [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . For this reason, parallel programming libraries like MPI contain standard reduction primitives with optimized implementations to aid efficient programming [CITATION_4] . These implementations typically take the form of a tree. Also, because the completion time of the reduction is dependent on many levels of network communications, the effects of our different timeout strategies are readily apparent.",
